Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of technology, specifically wearable biometric logging devices, for nutritional assessment. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as well as cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses issues with current methods for collecting nutritional data, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for analyzing food images.
